##Overview
This project demonstrates the concept of Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) in Java by creating a Book class and a main application called BookApp.
The program defines book details like title, author, and publication year, and displays the information in a formatted way using a method.
Features
Uses a constructor to initialize book attributes
Implements a displayBookInfo() method to print book details
Demonstrates object creation and method calling in Java
Prints book information clearly with line breaks between entries
